✨”Only you have the power to change your LIFE … and it starts by changing your habits.”✨

A couple of years ago, I went trough a hard and difficult time dealing with anxiety and depression . I knew I needed to change up habits that were not helping me the person God intended me to be .
I felt very lazy, tired, sad all the time. I had no goals, nothing that encouraged me at all. Depression is never silent , it actually becomes  very loud in your head and it take over your whole body if you allow it. 

I came to understand that I was the only one that could change my life. 
I decided I wanted something different, but different results never come from doing the same thing. 
I wanted a healthier life , a positive life and be a positive influence to others . So I started to set healthier habits and  made them part of my daily routines. Healing  is a process that is worth being patient trough. 
I saw my life turn around the moment I decide to step out in faith and make a change . 

If you are going to commit to something, Commit to yourself! Change is never comes easy, you will face challenges but you need to keep showing up for yourself because you are worth it. 🫶🏻

#healthylifestyle#halthyhabits#wellnesslifestyle#inspirational#2023goals#selfgrowthjourney #bestversionofyou #nightroutine#mindbodyspirit #faithandfitness#jesusisking#asmrmakeup

💭Night thoughts 💭

Have you ever gone to the gym and seen someone you wished you looked like and feel a bit discouraged with yourself?? 😓

I remember going  to the gym and seeing beautiful girls with amazing bodies and just feeling so bad with myself , at times I would even just leave the gym, because there was a feeling of embarrassment. My self esteem was just sooo low. 🥲

I realized it was not just about my physical appearance that I was unhappy about , It was everything. I needed more self love .  I came to realize  that feeling sorry for myself was not going to change anything. I decided I was done putting myself down and I was going to shift my focus and encourage my self. Work on myself , take care of myself and most important love  myself. 
 
In my healing journey, I have learned these things : 
🫶🏻Self motivation is another form of self love! 
✍🏻Write down and focus on your goals!
🙏🏻Pray and ask God to help you achieve those goals , we need Him !
👍🏻Cheer others around you along the way. 
👭No one is your competition , they are your encouragement. 
💪🏻Encourage and help others in their journey. (We all need it❤️)

I don’t know who needs to hear this , 
But this is your season !!!! ✨🙌🏻

When  Covid pandemic started in 2020 and we were all stuck at home , I found myself facing  a very hard battle  with severe depression and anxiety ( it’s a battle I had been fighting for years on and off). By then , God had already been talking to me trough many people , giving me direct words of prophecy. 
God put a stir in my heart to get on my social media and use the platform I had to share about Him. I deleted everything I had and start new with new uplifting content of encouragement and faith. At that moment, to me it seemed a bit ironic because I  needed those uplifting words of encouragement. I thought to myself, how can I encourage someone , when I feel so un-motivated myself . 

God helped  me understand that it’s the same things that the enemy wants to use against us , to destroys us , the same ones He will use for His glory to lift us up and they will become part of our testimony to reach others . 

The dream God has put in your heart , is not only with the purpose to bless your life , but to bless many others trough you . 

Stop thinking that God can’t use because you don’t feel qualified…coming from someone who was a Luke warm christian , a constant sinner, a depressed, divorced person full of mistakes , God can restore and use anyone he pleases . 

What is God calling you to do? 🙏🏻

.

How do you study the Bible? ✝️📖

Many of you asked me what resources I used to study the word of God. I honestly don’t believe there is a right or wrong way of doing so, but there are many resources we can use to help us better understand the Bible. 

Everyone has their own way of studying find what is best for you. 😌
For me what helped me was getting a Study Bible, this type of Bible provides references , dates , timelines, glossary and further explanation. 
Another source I use is @youversion bible app (which is a free app by the way ).
I love that it’s a fully equipped app with different versions of the Bible and it’s in different languages. 
My favorite part of the app is that it will help you study the word of God according to topics ; wether it’s depression , anxiety , grief , dating , ect ect . There are many different study plans with devotional included . 🙏🏻🙌🏻 
.
If you have any questions feel free to ask.

There is a story in the Bible where Jesus defends a woman who was caught in sin. 
While everyone around her accused her and the “religious people” condemned her, Jesus stoop up to defend her. 

This story stirs my heart so much, because I know what’s it like to be in her place. 
I remember after my divorce I found myself to be so broken spiritually and emotionally. 
I had so many people questioning the situation, others judging me behind my back… And every single comment broke my spirit a little bit more , till the point I felt there was no grace left for me ! I remember throwing myself on the shower floor , praying to God with no words, just tears. In that low moment of my life, I came to know a God so full of Grace , Mercy and Love. 
The only that could judge me , the only one free from sin , hugged me and lifted me up. 

You may have fallen and maybe the “religious people” have accused you and instead of lifting you up, they have left you on the ground, needing mercy. 
But I want to remind you that the only one that could ever judge you, gave his life for you,  because he loves you! 
All the Grace you need , you already have it trough Jesus Christ 🙏🏻❤️

.
.

GOD INTERRUPTED ME! 😓

Yesterday we locked ourselves outside the house 😅
It was so frustrating because i literally had a million things to get done. So while my love was trying to get the door open, i went for a little walk cause i needed to calm myself down 🥲 (being the impatient person i am ).
God interrupted me half trough my walk and told me to look up. I saw the most beautiful canvas in the sky. 
I had the most beautiful scenery right in-front of  me and i hadn’t noticed it because i was upset for what happened. I took a photo and well my hair was a mess, had a huge t shirt, so i tried to fix myself up but the moment was gone . 
The beautiful sky got dark and it was night time. The moment had passed with the clouds . Fast. 

I felt God speaking to my heart saying “ Its good and necessary  to pause and look around you. Enjoy your life and your present as it is. It doesn’t have to be perfect. Enjoy it while you can, because once it passes, you will never get those moments again.”
❤️🙏🏻.
.
